    "summary": "AN ACT TO AMEND SECTION 45-3-21, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, TO AUTHORIZE THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY TO INVESTIGATE THE DEATH OF ANY FORMER OR SITTING LOCAL, MUNICIPAL, COUNTY OR STATE OFFICIAL UNDER CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES; TO NAME THE PROVISIONS OF THIS ACT THE \"REPRESENTATIVE ASHLEY HENLEY INVESTIGATION AUTHORITY ACT\"; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
